# .env.example — the source-of-truth list of environment variables this repo needs.
#
# HOW THIS WORKS
#   • This file is committed. It documents EVERY variable the project reads, with a
#     comment saying what it is and where to get it — but never a real value.
#   • Copy it to a git-ignored `.env` and fill in the real secrets for local dev:
#         cp .env.example .env
#   • When you add a variable in code, add it here too (blank, documented). This file
#     is the checklist a new contributor works down to get running.
#
# This is a convention, not machinery — nothing in WongStack reads this file or requires
# a particular platform. Rename `.env`/`.env.example` to whatever your stack expects
# (e.g. a framework's own dotenv file) and keep the same discipline.

# --- Example entries (delete these; replace with your project's real variables) ---

# The base URL of the API this app talks to. Get it from your deploy dashboard.
# API_BASE_URL=

# A personal access token with read access. Create one at <provider> → Settings → Tokens.
# Treat it like a password — never commit the filled-in value.
# API_TOKEN=
